WEBVTT

00:02.080 --> 00:03.525
<i>Previously on</i> Justified...

00:03.600 --> 00:06.922
Never saw a pizza place with a...
What is that thing?

00:07.000 --> 00:08.080
It's a bank vault.

00:08.440 --> 00:10.522
There ain't no version of
this story that ends with

00:10.600 --> 00:12.921
us selling our home
to some peacock.

00:13.240 --> 00:14.969
You call me
a peacock?

00:15.080 --> 00:16.809
How's Ava doing, Boyd?

00:16.880 --> 00:17.961
It must have been quite a shock,

00:18.080 --> 00:20.082
her getting out of
prison the way she did.

00:20.640 --> 00:22.404
We can't gang up
on him, Katherine.

00:22.480 --> 00:24.847
You're as concerned about
her release as I was.

00:25.440 --> 00:27.090
It is outlining
the terms of your

00:27.160 --> 00:30.050
confidential informant arrangement
with the U.S. Attorney's office

00:30.120 --> 00:32.487
where you stipulate
that you will obtain

00:32.560 --> 00:35.530
relevant information that may lead
to charges against Boyd Crowder.

00:35.600 --> 00:38.410
I was enjoying my
morning constitutional,

00:38.480 --> 00:40.687
and lo and behold,
what do I find

00:40.760 --> 00:42.125
<i>but a stack of real estate deeds</i>

00:42.200 --> 00:44.931
<i>and a ledger that
I believe belong to you.</i>

00:45.000 --> 00:47.207
Since you got out,
sometimes I feel like

00:47.280 --> 00:48.805
I don't know
who you are anymore.

00:49.920 --> 00:51.081
Tell you what.

00:51.160 --> 00:53.811
You come on over here,
and I'll remind you.

01:15.880 --> 01:18.770
Morning.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.287
Are you off somewhere?
I am.

01:23.320 --> 01:25.926
Thought about letting you sleep,

01:26.000 --> 01:28.321
take full advantage
of this king size.

01:29.440 --> 01:32.125
Sneaking out just
didn't seem right. Mmm.

01:32.800 --> 01:34.689
When you think you'll be back?

01:34.760 --> 01:37.081
Little bit?
You gone all day?

01:37.520 --> 01:39.090
I'll be back this afternoon.

01:39.200 --> 01:40.884
Good.
Good?

01:40.960 --> 01:43.930
Wait a second. Ain't
that supposed to be bad?

01:45.680 --> 01:47.728
No. I was just thinking

01:48.040 --> 01:50.088
take advantage,
see about a massage.

01:50.160 --> 01:51.764
I don't know.
Something nice.

01:51.880 --> 01:53.370
Getting used
to the good life, uh?

01:53.440 --> 01:54.441
Mmm-hmm.
Well,

01:54.520 --> 01:56.090
go on.

01:56.160 --> 01:59.482
I'm just happy I got to hear
your voice before I go.

02:03.200 --> 02:04.281
Wait.

02:09.639 --> 02:10.721
Be careful.

02:11.039 --> 02:12.201
Always.

02:44.560 --> 02:46.528
What brings you to Lexington?

02:46.600 --> 02:48.967
Boyd came to meet his masters.

02:49.040 --> 02:50.326
And he brought you along?

02:50.440 --> 02:53.683
Oh, he sprung for
the lovebird package.

02:53.760 --> 02:56.047
Ava, if you're trying to tell
me you're sleeping with him,

02:56.120 --> 02:57.770
just so we're clear,

02:57.840 --> 02:59.524
I ain't asking you to do that.

02:59.600 --> 03:01.045
Are you asking me not to?

03:01.880 --> 03:03.848
I understand you got to do
what you got to do

03:03.920 --> 03:05.365
in a situation like yours.

03:05.440 --> 03:07.283
You think everything
is something else.

03:07.360 --> 03:08.640
You don't think
it could be real?

03:09.480 --> 03:10.720
I'm a person.

03:10.800 --> 03:12.404
I get lonely, scared.

03:12.480 --> 03:14.164
Remind me why we're here.

03:14.240 --> 03:16.049
You mean in this stairwell

03:16.120 --> 03:20.045
instead of a room, two
of us, champagne on ice?

03:29.760 --> 03:32.604
What's it like, holding
someone's fate in your hands?

03:33.480 --> 03:35.448
Drinking make you
a deep thinker?

03:35.520 --> 03:36.646
Oh, I'm straight.

03:36.720 --> 03:39.166
I want to know is it a burden,

03:39.280 --> 03:41.487
or is it what gets you
out of bed in the morning?

03:41.560 --> 03:43.528
What gets me out of bed lately

03:43.600 --> 03:45.762
is helping you fulfill
your agreement with us

03:45.840 --> 03:47.649
so you don't have
to go back to prison.

03:51.080 --> 03:54.368
Avery Markham paid us
a visit yesterday.

03:57.520 --> 03:59.010
Sounds vaguely familiar.

04:00.480 --> 04:02.084
Has a smell of sulfur to him.

04:02.160 --> 04:04.447
Boyd knew him by reputation.

04:04.520 --> 04:05.681
Seemed respectful.

04:06.240 --> 04:07.480
So it wasn't a friendly chat.

04:09.760 --> 04:12.650
He brought along
a real psycho case.

04:12.720 --> 04:14.609
Warned Boyd off
any future pursuits.

04:15.720 --> 04:17.084
Dyed hair, bushy beard?

04:18.760 --> 04:22.287
So, Boyd thought he was pulling
off a small potatoes heist,

04:22.360 --> 04:26.445
and what he was doing was
pissing off the big bad wolf.

04:27.240 --> 04:28.366
This helps, don't it?

04:29.480 --> 04:31.164
Nice to put a face
to the shot caller.

04:32.040 --> 04:33.121
So...

04:34.800 --> 04:39.362
Don't say you and me don't
have a special relationship.

04:40.000 --> 04:41.126
Did I say that?

04:43.720 --> 04:45.085
Boyd must be wetting his pants

04:45.160 --> 04:48.528
thinking about all them
piles and piles of money.

04:50.840 --> 04:52.808
No wonder you're scared.

05:02.760 --> 05:03.966
I'm so sorry, darling.

05:04.040 --> 05:06.486
I didn't mean to startle you.

05:06.560 --> 05:07.721
Can I help you?

05:07.840 --> 05:09.763
Where's my manners?

05:09.840 --> 05:10.966
I'm Katherine Hale.

05:11.080 --> 05:13.082
They gave me a key 'cause
I'm paying for the room.

05:13.560 --> 05:14.721
I did call you,

05:14.800 --> 05:16.643
but, um, you didn't pick up.

05:17.800 --> 05:19.882
I was just out having a smoke.

05:20.080 --> 05:21.650
Ah.

05:21.720 --> 05:25.930
Anyway, I thought it would be
nice if you and I had lunch.

05:27.320 --> 05:28.446
Okay.
Great.

05:29.760 --> 05:32.491
I'll order room service
to my suite.

05:32.600 --> 05:33.886
Noon?

05:33.960 --> 05:35.166
Sure.

05:35.240 --> 05:36.287
423.

05:36.840 --> 05:38.649
Did you forget your cigarettes?

05:38.720 --> 05:39.846
Excuse me?

05:40.680 --> 05:42.364
When you went out.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.923
I just smoke 'em one at a time.

05:48.920 --> 05:51.890
Next time you step out for
one, you let me know.

05:51.960 --> 05:56.648
I don't smoke anymore, but I love
standing next to people who still do.

05:56.760 --> 05:58.364
Okay.

05:58.440 --> 05:59.441
Next time.

06:04.760 --> 06:08.401
I don't have too much
unofficial case memory, Raylan.

06:08.480 --> 06:10.881
Just give me whatever your
addled old brain can muster.

06:11.440 --> 06:15.081
I pulled in a few of Markham's
men over the years.

06:15.160 --> 06:18.209
Maybe one or two run-ins
with the man himself, but...

06:18.960 --> 06:20.121
14 years ago.

06:20.200 --> 06:21.770
Why are you so crotchety?

06:21.840 --> 06:25.049
Don't act like you ain't thrilled to
use your old cop head for a minute,

06:25.120 --> 06:27.930
or did you want to get back to
the 400th hour of cable news?

06:28.240 --> 06:30.720
It obviously hasn't occurred
to you that this pain bullshit

06:30.800 --> 06:32.480
gets in the way of
a lot of clear thinking.

06:33.760 --> 06:35.285
I apologize.
Not to mention

06:35.360 --> 06:37.806
the fact that Leslie's been
waiting on me hand and foot

06:37.880 --> 06:41.089
and feeling sorry for me,
and that shit gets old.

06:41.440 --> 06:43.602
And I know she's sick of me,
and I know she'd rather be

06:43.680 --> 06:45.330
doing yoga with her
hippie friends,

06:45.400 --> 06:47.562
so I had to practically
shove her out the door,

06:47.640 --> 06:51.247
'cause I'm hungry and I'm sick
of eating all of her healthy

06:51.320 --> 06:53.004
twigs and cat food and shit.

06:53.280 --> 06:55.169
Well, you tell her
I said hey, uh?

06:55.360 --> 07:00.890
Grady Hale and Markham, his partner,
made their mint slinging weed.

07:01.000 --> 07:03.685
Grady Hale being Katherine
Hale's husband? Yeah.

07:03.920 --> 07:06.082
And when Grady Hale
went to jail,

07:06.160 --> 07:08.845
Markham went nobody knew where.

07:08.920 --> 07:10.922
You saying Markham flipped?

07:11.000 --> 07:12.047
Somebody did.

07:12.680 --> 07:14.842
As far as I know, the only
person that ever knew

07:14.920 --> 07:18.367
the name of the snitch was U.S.
Attorney Simon Poole,

07:18.440 --> 07:20.886
and he forgot that when
they blew half his head off

07:21.000 --> 07:23.924
with a shotgun on the corner
of Limestone and Barr.

07:24.760 --> 07:26.091
Was Markham a rat?

07:27.280 --> 07:29.886
Seems like Poole
let it slip one time that

07:29.960 --> 07:32.725
his snitch was out of the
weed business, but...

07:33.840 --> 07:37.367
You know, maybe when my
cable runs out, I'll look into it.

07:38.240 --> 07:39.321
Hmm.

07:41.040 --> 07:42.929
Now, that's how
you fry a damn egg.

07:43.000 --> 07:44.047
Why?

07:44.120 --> 07:45.485
Why what?
Any of it.

07:46.920 --> 07:48.445
What's it all mean?

07:48.520 --> 07:50.488
Well, you're gonna nail Boyd
Crowder and move to Florida,

07:50.560 --> 07:52.403
what do you care?
It's interesting.

07:52.680 --> 07:54.603
Spins this thing a whole
another way, hmm?

07:54.680 --> 07:56.205
Mmm-hmm.

07:56.280 --> 07:58.806
Sheds new light on an
ever spreading circle of

07:58.880 --> 08:01.360
greed and evil
and murder and mayhem.

08:01.440 --> 08:02.885
Oh, okay.

08:03.720 --> 08:06.007
When you stray from
the trail, Raylan,

08:06.080 --> 08:07.445
that's when you get lost.

08:07.880 --> 08:09.803
I know that, Art.
I do.

08:10.840 --> 08:13.286
But something's pulling me on.
Mmm-hmm.

08:13.720 --> 08:17.008
Something's pulling you away from nailing
Boyd and getting down to Florida.

08:17.080 --> 08:18.161
Your mama asks you
to take out the trash,

08:18.240 --> 08:21.050
you do as she says, but you see
a copperhead on the way out,

08:21.120 --> 08:23.691
you don't go back inside,
say you didn't do nothing,

08:23.760 --> 08:26.650
because all she asked
was take out the trash.

08:26.720 --> 08:28.927
You take out the trash
and the snake.

08:29.240 --> 08:31.891
Didn't your mama ever tell you
that there's always another snake?

08:32.799 --> 08:34.039
I knew you'd say that.

08:34.120 --> 08:37.363
Raylan, if you declare
war on them all,

08:37.440 --> 08:40.443
they're just gonna
outbreed you and outlast you

08:40.520 --> 08:41.885
and bring you down for good.

08:42.000 --> 08:43.967
You telling me
not to do the job?

08:44.760 --> 08:45.807
No.

08:47.120 --> 08:49.885
I'm telling you not
to get your ass bit.

09:22.280 --> 09:24.203
We can't make sense
of your CYA book.

09:25.120 --> 09:28.203
Safe to assume the names
herein are landowners?

09:32.160 --> 09:33.525
This room ain't bugged.

09:33.600 --> 09:35.250
Won't nobody know we spoke.

09:36.000 --> 09:37.161
These landowners are
in the ledger

09:37.240 --> 09:39.208
'cause Avery Markham
has designs on buying?

09:41.240 --> 09:42.480
Or has already bought.

09:42.640 --> 09:44.768
How many? How many have
lines through them?

09:44.840 --> 09:46.251
Many.

09:46.320 --> 09:48.971
A line through a name means...

09:51.360 --> 09:53.283
Cash was offered and accepted.

09:53.360 --> 09:55.601
What's it mean a name has a
line through it and a circle?

09:55.680 --> 09:59.082
Means first offer declined,
counteroffer accepted.

09:59.200 --> 10:01.567
Red Crowell's name was circled
and a line through it.

10:01.640 --> 10:02.926
How'd you sweeten the deal?

10:03.000 --> 10:04.490
Upped the offer $50,000.

10:04.560 --> 10:05.561
Nothing else?

10:06.040 --> 10:08.042
You know there was
a fire there a week ago?

10:09.000 --> 10:10.047
Sad.

10:10.800 --> 10:13.963
Red lost everything. Had to move
in with his kin down in Nashville.

10:14.040 --> 10:15.121
We stopped by.

10:15.200 --> 10:16.884
Place burned to the
concrete footings.

10:17.160 --> 10:20.562
The house was a wreck. There was
wires hanging out everywhere.

10:20.680 --> 10:21.727
Mess, too.

10:22.200 --> 10:24.123
Looked like he was
hoarding for the rapture.

10:24.200 --> 10:26.407
Talked to the chief.
He ruled out foul play,

10:26.520 --> 10:29.285
though he did note there were
more fires in town as of late.

10:29.360 --> 10:33.206
Murphy's law, simplest
explanation is usually correct.

10:33.320 --> 10:34.651
You mean Occam's razor.

10:34.720 --> 10:37.485
Occam's razor, Thor's
hammer, who gives a shit?

10:37.560 --> 10:40.689
Like as not, it's folks
looking for the insurance.

10:40.760 --> 10:42.569
No, not Red Crowell.

10:43.520 --> 10:47.411
Look, they're big talkers,
but that's real estate.

10:47.640 --> 10:48.880
I don't think they're bad men.

10:49.000 --> 10:51.731
And yet you're spooked so much
that we got to pull it out of you.

10:52.040 --> 10:54.327
I'm just saying
Markham wants land,

10:54.400 --> 10:56.050
he doesn't have to work
that hard for it.

10:56.120 --> 10:58.407
He goes five miles
down the road.

10:58.480 --> 10:59.845
He can buy whatever he wants.

10:59.920 --> 11:03.163
Not if the pot king of Colorado's
got his sights set on Harlan.

11:03.240 --> 11:04.730
If he and his coadjutors

11:04.800 --> 11:06.689
want to seize an opportunity

11:06.760 --> 11:09.240
in the land of the
Christmas tree weed,

11:09.320 --> 11:11.004
who are we to fetter progress?

11:11.080 --> 11:14.004
Don't give a shit about
his business agenda.

11:14.080 --> 11:17.209
Though I worry about those
who stand in his way.

11:17.760 --> 11:19.603
That include you.

11:19.680 --> 11:21.728
Look, fellas, I've
been helpful, right?

11:22.040 --> 11:23.724
Are we wrapping this up?

11:23.800 --> 11:25.370
I have a speech to write.

11:26.440 --> 11:28.727
Twisting my stomach in knots.

11:28.800 --> 11:30.131
Running for mayor again?

11:30.360 --> 11:32.044
No. I've had
a rough day.

11:32.120 --> 11:34.487
I have to eulogize
a friend tonight.

11:34.560 --> 11:36.369
Sorry to hear it.
Pillar of the community.

11:36.800 --> 11:39.451
She and her husband died in
the damn strangest accident.

11:41.800 --> 11:42.961
What kind of accident?

11:43.280 --> 11:45.089
Furnace took a shit.

11:45.760 --> 11:48.286
Carbon monoxide killed
them both in their sleep.

11:49.080 --> 11:50.286
Who we talking about?

11:50.480 --> 11:52.164
Betty and John-O Hutchins.

11:53.040 --> 11:54.690
Betty Hutchins
the English teacher?

11:54.760 --> 11:55.886
Same.

11:55.960 --> 11:57.769
Hutchins was a name on the list.

11:58.600 --> 12:00.762
Circled and X'd out.

12:01.480 --> 12:05.246
That means more than
one offer was made.

12:05.320 --> 12:06.810
Both refused.

12:11.160 --> 12:12.969
You were a cheerleader
in high school.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.081
I was.

12:15.160 --> 12:16.924
I always wanted
to be a cheerleader.

12:17.000 --> 12:18.001
Football games,

12:18.360 --> 12:21.682
I'd sit high up in those stands

12:21.800 --> 12:25.202
and watch those girls
bouncing in their skirts,

12:25.280 --> 12:26.645
see how all the players

12:27.160 --> 12:29.970
well, everyone, really,

12:30.040 --> 12:32.168
was just mesmerized by them.

12:32.640 --> 12:35.610
It was a lot of work. We
practiced five days a week.

12:35.680 --> 12:37.762
What power those girls had.

12:39.840 --> 12:42.525
Yet so few knew how to use it.

12:43.720 --> 12:46.291
But you did, huh?

12:47.200 --> 12:50.409
You got one of those football
players to marry you.

12:50.480 --> 12:51.641
I did.

12:52.920 --> 12:54.604
Doesn't mean I had
any real power.

12:55.200 --> 12:57.407
Because he beat you senseless?

12:59.680 --> 13:00.966
You know a lot about me.

13:01.520 --> 13:04.364
I know you blew
a hole through his chest.

13:05.480 --> 13:08.723
Did you invite me to lunch
to talk about my past?

13:10.040 --> 13:12.850
I invited you to lunch
to ask you a question.

13:13.720 --> 13:16.530
I'm not sure I want to hear it.

13:17.280 --> 13:19.886
I was married to Grady
for 20 years.

13:20.200 --> 13:23.443
And I loved that man
with all my heart.

13:23.520 --> 13:25.887
But there were days...

13:26.440 --> 13:28.249
Weeks...

13:29.040 --> 13:30.565
Months, really.

13:33.560 --> 13:35.801
My question is this

13:37.040 --> 13:41.443
when you pulled that
trigger, how did it feel?

13:42.960 --> 13:45.406
'Cause I have to think
it felt great.

13:50.520 --> 13:53.251
Are you wondering
what's under here?

13:55.120 --> 13:57.043
Should I be?

13:57.120 --> 13:59.600
It is the best part
of this lunch.

14:08.040 --> 14:09.610
That's never been my thing.

14:12.120 --> 14:15.283
Well, darling,
this is the good stuff.

14:15.800 --> 14:18.804
This is pharmaceutical grade.
And believe me...

14:19.400 --> 14:22.483
You are gonna need it
for what I've got planned.

14:22.560 --> 14:26.360
None of the barons can deposit
in legit FDIC backed banks,

14:26.440 --> 14:29.444
marijuana being legal
only at the state level.

14:29.800 --> 14:33.407
Hence mercenaries guarding
a pizza place full of dough.

14:35.320 --> 14:37.209
Did you see what I did there?

14:37.280 --> 14:40.887
Well, a man's wit is never
lost on me, Wynn Duffy. Hey.

14:42.280 --> 14:44.362
So, you're telling me that
Avery Markham really believes

14:44.440 --> 14:46.283
that legal weed is coming
to the state of Kentucky?

14:46.360 --> 14:48.249
Probably sooner than later.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.049
The way the smoke's blowing.

14:50.920 --> 14:54.686
FYI, my guy's a handful,
irritating.

14:54.760 --> 14:57.730
His brain's fried from who
knows what kind of drugs.

14:57.800 --> 15:00.326
You're gonna want to punch
him, but he's very good.

15:01.600 --> 15:03.728
I'm saying have fun with it.

15:10.840 --> 15:12.285
They're here, baby.

15:12.520 --> 15:14.921
Looky here!

15:15.000 --> 15:16.126
Wynn Duffy!

15:16.920 --> 15:18.126
You're looking healthy.

15:18.200 --> 15:19.611
Been a long time.

15:19.680 --> 15:22.524
What can I say? I save you for the
big jobs, man of your talent.

15:22.600 --> 15:24.409
Oh, yeah.
And my price.

15:24.520 --> 15:26.761
- You must be the man with the vault problem.
- Now, Mr. Wiz,

15:26.840 --> 15:29.684
I prefer discussing
my business in private.

15:29.800 --> 15:31.245
Bridge is cool.

15:31.320 --> 15:32.606
I didn't say she wasn't cool.

15:34.520 --> 15:35.931
What's the matter?

15:36.000 --> 15:37.161
Rudy likes you.

15:39.360 --> 15:41.806
So, uh, just spitballing
on the ride over,

15:41.880 --> 15:43.689
we were thinking, uh, Emulex?

15:46.320 --> 15:47.526
Emulex?

15:47.600 --> 15:51.241
Emulex to blow
an Excelsior 5200?

15:51.320 --> 15:53.288
That was part of the plan, yeah.

15:53.360 --> 15:55.283
Are you ser...
Oh, my God.

15:55.360 --> 15:57.567
Excelsior's old school!

15:57.640 --> 16:00.484
It's 16 inches of
Youngstown steel, dude.

16:00.560 --> 16:01.766
You need something massive

16:01.880 --> 16:03.769
C-4?
To get through that shit.

16:03.840 --> 16:06.684
No, man, I'm talking,
like, C-11, dude.

16:06.760 --> 16:09.730
New military issue, like
asymmetrical warfare shit.

16:09.880 --> 16:11.370
That shit only you got,
huh, baby?

16:11.440 --> 16:13.568
Damn straight
only the shit I got!

16:13.640 --> 16:14.846
And if they catch you with it,

16:14.920 --> 16:16.524
they're taking you
to Guantanamo Bay

16:16.600 --> 16:18.240
and hooking your nuts up
to a car battery.

16:18.480 --> 16:19.845
Oh!

16:19.920 --> 16:21.206
Where's my manners?

16:21.280 --> 16:22.691
Would you guys like a Negroni?

16:22.720 --> 16:24.290
I don't know what that is.
It's Italian.

16:24.360 --> 16:25.960
Tastes like grapefruit.
I don't want one.

16:26.000 --> 16:27.411
Missing out.

16:29.880 --> 16:31.484
