work a day in your life.

27:41.920 --> 27:44.287
I like to drink when I think.

27:44.360 --> 27:45.407
Care to join?

27:45.920 --> 27:47.046
Sure.

27:49.200 --> 27:51.441
I got this from a dear friend.

27:52.880 --> 27:54.530
She called it apple pie.

27:54.600 --> 27:55.931
Not too sweet, I hope.

27:57.080 --> 27:59.048
Too sweet gives me a headache.

27:59.600 --> 28:01.489
It's not sweet, but...

28:03.040 --> 28:04.963
It might still give you
a headache.

28:22.520 --> 28:23.567
What's this shit?

28:24.280 --> 28:26.203
Good evening to you,
too, Loretta.

28:26.280 --> 28:27.327
Can we talk?

28:27.400 --> 28:28.606
She's right
in the middle of something.

28:28.760 --> 28:29.841
That doesn't bother us.

28:30.360 --> 28:31.885
Actually, we're done.

28:31.960 --> 28:33.520
But that don't mean
I feel like talking.

28:33.800 --> 28:35.928
Done?
No, we're not done.

28:36.200 --> 28:37.565
Don't be silly.

28:37.640 --> 28:38.801
Oh, we're done.

28:38.880 --> 28:41.406
I was about to pour you
a drink and show you out.

28:41.880 --> 28:43.080
So you're rejecting our offer?

28:43.280 --> 28:44.441
I am.

28:44.640 --> 28:47.166
But we didn't even negotiate.

28:47.240 --> 28:48.844
- No means no.
- Hey!

28:48.920 --> 28:50.081
I'm not talking to you.

28:50.560 --> 28:51.846
Loretta, do me a favor.

28:52.440 --> 28:54.169
Take a big old step
to your right.

28:58.520 --> 28:59.601
Okay.

28:59.680 --> 29:01.842
You ain't talking to me.
She's done talking to you.

29:02.760 --> 29:04.171
Now, you want to
get your ass out,

29:04.240 --> 29:06.000
or is there something else
you're here to do?

29:17.680 --> 29:18.681
Mr. Markham.

29:38.280 --> 29:39.691
Avery Markham, I presume.

29:40.160 --> 29:41.730
You must be Givens.

29:42.040 --> 29:43.883
Deputy U.S. Marshal Givens.

29:45.480 --> 29:47.528
This young woman
must be Loretta.

29:48.040 --> 29:49.690
Pleased to meet you, Miss.

29:49.920 --> 29:52.810
Though I envisioned it under
different circumstances.

29:54.560 --> 29:57.689
Why don't we sit down, have
a civilized conversation?

29:58.120 --> 29:59.201
We'll be brief.

29:59.280 --> 30:02.682
Well, these bones
are gonna take a chair

30:03.560 --> 30:04.686
either way.

30:08.280 --> 30:10.248
Well, what have we here?

30:11.760 --> 30:13.364
Mmm.

30:13.440 --> 30:14.601
That takes me back.

30:15.080 --> 30:16.684
This yours?
Yes, sir.

30:16.760 --> 30:18.524
You mind?
Of course not.

30:20.000 --> 30:21.081
Go ahead, darling.

30:21.280 --> 30:23.806
Stick your little pinkie
in there and have a lick.

30:35.960 --> 30:37.291
Okay, now.

30:38.320 --> 30:41.449
I'll give you this. You've
done your homework.

30:44.240 --> 30:46.129
Homework, hell.

30:46.240 --> 30:47.924
I'm a corn cracker
through and through.

30:48.720 --> 30:50.449
Grew up with
my hands in the dirt.

30:51.280 --> 30:53.931
My daddy was a 'bacca
farmer out in Cynthiana,

30:55.560 --> 30:57.130
raising up burley.

30:57.200 --> 30:58.770
Traded one leaf for another.

31:02.800 --> 31:06.122
I've spent many days
in this neck of the woods.

31:07.480 --> 31:08.891
Knew Miss McCready's daddy

31:09.600 --> 31:11.125
and her mama.

31:11.240 --> 31:14.323
Bennetts, too,
us being in the same line.

31:16.200 --> 31:19.841
How I knew to check
that glass, darlin'.

31:22.440 --> 31:25.410
I knew a Crowder or two,

31:25.480 --> 31:27.642
but no one
by the name of Givens.

31:27.960 --> 31:31.043
Arlo's wannabe kingpin ass
would be heartbroken.

31:31.120 --> 31:34.602
Six generations of Bennetts
grew up in Harlan County.

31:35.440 --> 31:38.364
Now all's left is
a cripple stuck in lockup.

31:40.000 --> 31:41.923
Story is that's thanks to you.

31:42.640 --> 31:44.529
The Bennetts were my problem.

31:44.600 --> 31:45.726
Now you are my problem.

31:45.840 --> 31:48.047
Somebody please tell me what
all you're talking about.

31:48.120 --> 31:51.567
The man is making you
an offer you can't refuse.

31:51.680 --> 31:53.364
Sell or he kills you.

31:53.440 --> 31:55.169
Oh, come on, now.

31:55.680 --> 31:58.047
I may make you an offer
you can't refuse.

31:58.120 --> 32:00.881
But that's because I'm offering you
more money than you ever imagined.

32:01.360 --> 32:03.488
And if I don't want it
at any price?

32:03.560 --> 32:06.131
Then you'd be a bird so rare

32:06.200 --> 32:09.363
as to never before
have been sighted.

32:09.440 --> 32:11.488
The negotiation has ended.

32:12.200 --> 32:14.407
I told you,
you can't have my land.

32:14.480 --> 32:15.606
I'm adding hers to the list.

32:16.680 --> 32:20.287
I don't see how you can do
that, legally speaking.

32:20.360 --> 32:22.761
You want to follow
that thread, be my guest.

32:22.840 --> 32:26.208
Till then, you can put away
your suitcase of money.

32:26.600 --> 32:28.125
Or what?

32:28.200 --> 32:30.441
You gonna give me 24 hours
to get out of town,

32:30.520 --> 32:33.126
Deputy U.S. Marshal
Raylan Givens?

32:33.200 --> 32:35.043
And he said he didn't
do his homework.

32:36.080 --> 32:38.890
I'm just saying there's
no deal to make here.

32:39.680 --> 32:42.081
First you turn me down.
Now this.

32:42.160 --> 32:43.650
What's next?

32:43.720 --> 32:44.767
Third time?

32:45.080 --> 32:47.765
You gonna tell me that,
by the power vested in you,

32:47.840 --> 32:50.286
that there's something else
I ain't allowed to do?

32:51.480 --> 32:53.448
This is still America,
last time I checked

32:53.520 --> 32:55.010
the flagpole.

32:55.480 --> 32:58.484
What's next is entirely based

32:58.560 --> 33:00.881
on the next choice you make.

33:09.200 --> 33:12.010
I think I'll burn one
on the way out.

33:12.080 --> 33:13.570
Helps me think.

33:15.800 --> 33:16.961
You gonna haul me in?

33:17.280 --> 33:19.328
No, not for weed.

33:19.400 --> 33:21.084
I can assure you of that.

33:26.400 --> 33:27.765
Okay, then.

33:29.080 --> 33:30.570
I'll be seeing you.

33:37.720 --> 33:39.006
Okay.

33:39.680 --> 33:42.047
Heard this one back in the '90s.

33:43.880 --> 33:45.848
Bill Clinton and Hillary

33:45.960 --> 33:48.167
sneak away from
the Secret Service

33:48.240 --> 33:51.210
and go for a drive,
backwoods Arkansas.

33:51.280 --> 33:54.807
And they come
to a gasoline station,

33:55.480 --> 33:57.687
and Hillary recognizes
the attendant,

33:57.760 --> 34:00.286
saying that was her
boyfriend before Bill.

34:00.800 --> 34:03.849
And Bill laughs, saying...

34:04.120 --> 34:08.920
"Imagine where you would be
now if you married that guy."

34:09.000 --> 34:11.650
And Hillary, quick
as a minute, says“.

34:12.360 --> 34:16.409
"I would be married to the
President of the United States."

34:19.080 --> 34:20.730
That's funny.
No.

34:21.239 --> 34:23.083
That's Grady and me.

34:23.920 --> 34:27.163
He was the face,
and I got it done.

34:30.880 --> 34:34.646
Must be frustrating,
Grady getting all the glory.

34:34.760 --> 34:35.966
Well...

34:36.960 --> 34:40.442
Taking his partner as my lover
made it a little easier.

34:40.800 --> 34:41.801
Avery Markham.

34:41.880 --> 34:45.009
Best lover I had ever had.

34:45.080 --> 34:46.320
Still is.

34:46.960 --> 34:50.168
Nevertheless, I know
he ratted out Grady

34:50.239 --> 34:54.449
and was responsible for
all that ensued, down to

34:54.520 --> 34:58.366
me pulling vindictive, low class,
little stunts in a jewelry store.

35:00.040 --> 35:02.122
Smart of you, though,

35:02.840 --> 35:04.649
sleeping with him.

35:04.720 --> 35:06.449
Can't imagine he'd suspect

35:06.520 --> 35:09.285
the man trying to rob him is
the woman underneath him.

35:09.760 --> 35:11.489
Not always underneath him.

35:13.680 --> 35:17.002
Yeah, I doubt that his money is
gonna feel as good as he does,

35:17.080 --> 35:20.766
but I sure cannot wait
to get my hands on it.

35:21.840 --> 35:25.845
I mean, a man as much
as kills your husband,

35:25.920 --> 35:28.048
you got to do
something about it.

35:29.040 --> 35:30.690
He killed Grady?

35:31.720 --> 35:35.725
Well, the prison assholes claimed
it was suicide, but...

35:36.520 --> 35:40.889
There was a lot of Dixie Mafia
muscle inside at that time,

35:40.960 --> 35:43.645
and those guys know how to fix
a murder to look like suicide

35:43.720 --> 35:45.324
easy as baking a pie.

35:49.240 --> 35:50.605
Oh, my goodness.

35:52.000 --> 35:53.650
That's my massage.

35:54.840 --> 35:56.251
I guess you better go.

35:56.920 --> 35:57.967
Oh.

35:58.760 --> 35:59.841
Okay.

36:05.240 --> 36:07.447
Thank you for a...

36:09.520 --> 36:11.409
A very interesting day.

36:12.080 --> 36:13.320
Anytime.

36:14.440 --> 36:15.487
Hey.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.241
It sure was lucky the way that

36:20.320 --> 36:24.530
guard of yours, the one
who said you stabbed him,

36:24.600 --> 36:28.366
how fortunate that he came
clean the way he did.

36:30.160 --> 36:32.322
What was his name? Uh...

36:32.400 --> 36:34.562
Albert Fekus?

36:34.640 --> 36:36.563
You ever thought about
thanking him?

36:38.160 --> 36:40.686
The guy was a crazy
piece of shit.

36:40.800 --> 36:42.529
All he did was finally
tell the truth.

36:42.600 --> 36:44.523
Yeah, but...

36:44.600 --> 36:47.922
Something made him step up

36:48.000 --> 36:50.446
and do the right thing, so...

36:51.920 --> 36:55.925
You know, if you ever want to get to the
bottom of his crisis of conscience,

36:56.000 --> 36:58.128
I could find him for you.

36:58.200 --> 36:59.770
It would be a breeze.

37:00.200 --> 37:02.248
Mmm.
That's so kind of you.

37:04.120 --> 37:06.805
But I'd probably just
stab him in the eye.

37:09.320 --> 37:10.970
You really are a firecracker.

37:20.840 --> 37:22.365
<i>Stop acting
like a badass</i>

37:22.440 --> 37:23.805
older than you are.

37:23.880 --> 37:25.689
Well, stop acting like my daddy.

37:25.760 --> 37:27.842
You're a kid.
Enjoy it.

37:28.120 --> 37:31.283
No need to take over the goddamn
world with your ambition.

37:31.360 --> 37:33.044
I don't even know how you're
thinking on this scale.

37:33.120 --> 37:35.885
What am I, stupid?
Look around.

37:35.960 --> 37:38.804
Five years, not even, it'll
be legal across the land.

37:38.880 --> 37:40.928
Oh, don't give me that bullshit.

37:41.000 --> 37:43.207
You're gonna sell dope
whether it's legal or not.

37:43.320 --> 37:44.970
But you set your sights
this high,

37:45.040 --> 37:46.840
you're gonna keep running
into folks like him.

37:46.880 --> 37:49.008
Is that what your daddy
would want?

37:53.200 --> 37:54.406
You didn't know him.

37:54.680 --> 37:56.170
Well, I know what
all daddies want.

37:56.240 --> 37:57.685
They want their kids to be safe.

38:00.040 --> 38:02.327
So, you're saying
walk away from weed?

38:02.400 --> 38:03.401
Look.

38:03.680 --> 38:05.569
It's good that you have goals.

38:05.880 --> 38:07.962
But for me, next couple weeks,

38:08.040 --> 38:10.611
just put two big guys out front.

38:11.040 --> 38:13.281
Help me sleep at night?

38:14.880 --> 38:16.370
Thanks for the heart to heart.

38:16.480 --> 38:18.244
Really changed my mind.
We done?

38:18.320 --> 38:21.051
Hmm'?
Uh, No.

38:21.520 --> 38:22.726
Loretta.

38:26.400 --> 38:27.481
God damn it.

38:28.400 --> 38:29.640
You mean to send three 5's?

38:29.720 --> 38:31.040
'Cause that's the
bat signal, Ava.

38:31.120 --> 38:33.240
That's what you send when a
grenade's about to go off.

38:33.280 --> 38:34.611
<i>Albert Fekus.</i>

38:34.840 --> 38:36.729
<i>What?</i>
She asked me about Fekus.

38:36.840 --> 38:38.683
You need to slow down.

38:39.200 --> 38:43.569
Katherine Hale asked me about
Albert Fekus, the guard!

38:43.640 --> 38:45.840
<i>The little shithead!</i> How the
hell did that even come up?

38:45.880 --> 38:47.370
Out of literally
goddamn nowhere.

38:47.440 --> 38:50.523
She just started asking why he
had a "crisis of conscience,"

38:50.640 --> 38:52.290
<i>why he changed his testimony.</i>

38:52.400 --> 38:55.882
Okay, at best, she's just testing you.
<i>I'm telling you...</i>

38:56.400 --> 38:57.845
She knows.
No.

38:57.920 --> 38:59.524
Trust me, she does not know.

38:59.800 --> 39:00.847
Why?

39:00.920 --> 39:04.003
Because she didn't put a bullet
in my head right then and there?

39:04.080 --> 39:06.128
Jesus Christ,
I have to get out of here.

39:06.200 --> 39:07.281
Where are you right now?

39:07.520 --> 39:09.090
I'm still in the hotel.
Okay.

39:09.200 --> 39:11.521
I want you to go down
to the Horseshoe Diner.

39:11.600 --> 39:13.520
Wait there. I'm gonna have
someone come meet you.

39:13.760 --> 39:15.205
Get where'?
<i>The Horseshoe Diner.</i>

39:15.280 --> 39:16.406
Shit.

39:16.560 --> 39:17.607
Ava?

39:21.120 --> 39:22.451
Hey, baby.

39:23.280 --> 39:24.327
Hey.

39:25.120 --> 39:26.929
You packing already?

39:27.440 --> 39:29.044
Thought I'd get a jump on it.

39:29.800 --> 39:32.087
We're heading home
tonight, right?

39:32.160 --> 39:33.730
Well, when they say
late checkout,

39:33.800 --> 39:35.689
I don't think they mean
10:00 at night.

39:37.440 --> 39:39.090
Are you sure

39:40.000 --> 39:44.369
you don't want to crawl
into this Egyptian cotton,

39:44.960 --> 39:47.531
order a pint of ice cream?

39:48.000 --> 39:49.445
Come on, now.

39:49.520 --> 39:50.965
They got free cable.

39:52.960 --> 39:55.566
I think I just want to get home,

39:55.640 --> 39:58.246
sleep in my...
In our own bed.

40:01.320 --> 40:02.651
All right.

40:05.000 --> 40:06.445
You Okay?

40:06.520 --> 40:08.648
Yeah, I'm fine.

40:08.760 --> 40:11.366
Duffy said that

40:11.440 --> 40:14.046
Katherine Hale wanted to
have lunch with you today.

40:14.280 --> 40:16.681
What did you two talk about?

40:16.760 --> 40:18.603
Mmm. Nothing.

40:18.680 --> 40:20.011
Nothing?

40:20.080 --> 40:21.923
Why, I didn't think it was
possible for two women

40:22.000 --> 40:23.604
to get together
and talk about nothing.

40:23.680 --> 40:25.808
She didn't talk about me?

40:25.880 --> 40:26.927
No.

40:27.360 --> 40:29.442
She didn't even bring up
how good-looking I am?

40:29.720 --> 40:31.245
No. She ju...

40:32.120 --> 40:33.451
We just had lunch.

40:33.720 --> 40:35.927
Well, I guess she was just

40:36.000 --> 40:39.209
looking forward to enjoying
the pleasure of your company.

40:40.040 --> 40:42.611
I can't say that I blame her.

40:42.680 --> 40:45.331
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

40:45.400 --> 40:46.731
Come here.

40:46.840 --> 40:48.330
Sit right here.

40:51.440 --> 40:53.329
Let me see them hands.

41:01.160 --> 41:02.366
Boyd, there's something that

41:03.200 --> 41:04.645
I need to talk to you about.

41:04.720 --> 41:07.200
Baby, I know what
you're gonna say.

41:07.600 --> 41:11.047
But before you do, I want to
tell you something first.

41:12.480 --> 41:14.767
I'm taking you home,

41:14.840 --> 41:17.571
and we never have to
leave Harlan County again.

41:17.680 --> 41:19.330
What do you mean?

41:20.160 --> 41:22.128
I got us a whole new endgame.

41:22.720 --> 41:24.768
Reason Markham's got that money

41:24.840 --> 41:28.401
he's looking to buy up land
to grow pot legally.

41:29.080 --> 41:31.040
Now, a man like him doesn't
make that kind of move

41:31.080 --> 41:33.321
unless he knows what's
coming around the corner.

41:33.400 --> 41:36.165
Now, I'm talking
about judges, baby.

41:36.240 --> 41:37.810
I'm talking about police.

41:37.880 --> 41:40.486
I'm talking about
State Senators.

41:40.600 --> 41:42.887
Now, I'm already on point
to steal his money.

41:42.960 --> 41:45.088
I'm gonna use it to
steal his idea, too.

41:45.200 --> 41:48.886
Boyd... Baby, legal weed
in the state of Kentucky.

41:50.920 --> 41:52.331
We're gonna make a killing.

41:52.720 --> 41:56.691
And we're gonna bring hope and prosperity
back to this beautiful county,

41:56.760 --> 41:59.684
our home, Harlan County,
once again.

41:59.960 --> 42:02.770
What happened to us
ending up on a beach?

42:03.240 --> 42:06.130
Come on, baby, you know how these
legs look in a bathing suit.

42:06.480 --> 42:07.766
Huh.

42:10.120 --> 42:12.441
We're gonna have it all, Ava,

42:12.520 --> 42:14.204
and we're gonna have it right
here in Harlan County.

42:14.280 --> 42:16.362
No running, no hiding.

42:17.720 --> 42:19.210
I don't know what to say.

42:19.280 --> 42:21.089
You ain't got to say anything.

42:22.040 --> 42:24.646
Now, I'm gonna take a shower.

42:24.720 --> 42:26.085
Then we're gonna hit the road,

42:26.160 --> 42:28.128
and I'm gonna have
you back in Harlan County

42:28.200 --> 42:29.770
before the sun comes up!

42:30.560 --> 42:31.971
Whoo!
